---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { SiteChromeBoot } from "../components/SiteChromeBoot";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Tonet"
  description="How usetonet.com and Tonet-related distribution handle personal data: hosting, downloads, local settings, and your rights."
  page="privacy"
>
  <main class="legal-page">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="legal-updated"><strong>Last updated:</strong> May 2, 2026</p>
    <p class="legal-lang-note" role="note">
      <strong>Language:</strong> This page is available in <strong>English only</strong>. It is not part of the site’s translated interface; the
      language selector in the footer only affects navigation labels on other pages.
    </p>

    <p>
      This policy describes how information is handled in connection with the Tonet project website (<strong>usetonet.com</strong>), public
      GitHub repositories, and the Tonet browser binaries we distribute. It is written to support transparency requirements (including the EU
      General Data Protection Regulation — GDPR) where they apply. The <strong>official language of this policy is English</strong>; translated
      summaries may be added later and will defer to the English text in case of conflict.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
    <p>
      Tonet is an <strong>open source</strong> browser project. The website and downloads are operated as a community/project publication. There
      is no physical office address for Tonet; we do not list corporate “office” locations on this site. For privacy requests or questions about
      this policy, use <a href="https://github.com/usetonet/tonet-browser/issues">GitHub Issues</a> on the public repository.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Scope</h2>
    <p>This policy covers:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>This marketing and documentation site (static pages served via Cloudflare Workers).</li>
      <li>Download infrastructure (e.g. CDN / manifest URLs documented in the project) when you fetch installers or version metadata.</li>
      <li>Interaction with GitHub when you visit or contribute to our repositories.</li>
      <li>Local settings stored by this website in your browser (site language preference).</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      It does not replace the privacy policies of third parties you may interact with while using Tonet to browse the web (for example, website
      operators, operating-system vendors, or search providers).
    </p>

    <h2>3. What we do not do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>We do not sell your personal data.</li>
      <li>We do not operate user accounts on this website.</li>
      <li>We do not run advertising analytics or cross-site tracking pixels on this static landing.</li>
      <li>
        The Tonet browser is designed as a <strong>minimal, transparent</strong> product; it does not implement the broad telemetry,
        sync, or rewards ecosystems found in many mainstream browsers. (See project docs for current capabilities.)
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Website hosting &amp; logs</h2>
    <p>
      The site is delivered through <strong>Cloudflare</strong> (Workers / CDN). As with any web host, Cloudflare and related infrastructure may
      process technical data such as IP address, TLS metadata, User-Agent, and request paths for security, reliability, and aggregate statistics.
      See <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cloudflare’s privacy policy</a> for
      details. We do not use this data to build individual profiles of visitors to usetonet.com.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Downloads &amp; update checks</h2>
    <p>
      When you download Tonet, your client retrieves binaries and may retrieve <strong>version manifests</strong> as described in the project
      documentation (including URLs you or your organization configure). Those requests are ordinary HTTPS transfers; the CDN or hosting provider
      may log technical data in line with their policies. We do not attach those logs to “accounts” on our side because we do not offer accounts.
    </p>

    <h2>6. GitHub</h2>
    <p>
      Source code and releases may be hosted on <strong>GitHub</strong>. If you open issues, pull requests, or clone repositories, Microsoft’s
      GitHub privacy terms apply. Do not post secrets or sensitive personal data in public issues.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Local storage (language preference)</h2>
    <p>
      The language selector on this site may store your choice in <code>localStorage</code> in your browser so the preference persists between
      visits. This is not used for tracking across sites. You can clear it using your browser’s settings.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Legal bases (GDPR)</h2>
    <p>Where GDPR applies, we rely on:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Legitimate interests</strong> in operating a secure public website and distributing open source software (Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR).</li>
      <li>
        <strong>Consent</strong> where required for strictly optional mechanisms (we currently do not use optional marketing cookies on this
        landing).
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>9. International transfers</h2>
    <p>
      Infrastructure providers (e.g. Cloudflare, GitHub) may process data in the United States and other countries. Where required, they use
      appropriate safeguards such as Standard Contractual Clauses. Review their policies for details.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights to access, rectify, erase, restrict, or object to processing of personal data, and to
      lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority. Because we collect minimal data, many requests may be limited to what appears in provider logs.
      Contact us via <a href="https://github.com/usetonet/tonet-browser/issues">GitHub Issues</a> for privacy-related requests; we will respond
      within a reasonable time.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Children</h2>
    <p>
      Tonet and this site are intended for a general audience and not directed at children under 16. We do not knowingly collect personal data
      from children for marketing purposes.
    </p>

    <h2>12. Changes</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy when practices change materially. The “Last updated” date at the top will change accordingly. Continued use of the
      site after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy where permitted by law.
    </p>
  </main>
  <SiteChromeBoot client:load />
</BaseLayout>
